^-{    ANOTHER WAY OF TAKING DISCARDS BEFORE LEADING TRUMPS    }
^-|CP||FP||AT|^B@2^Y@3I|FP||AT|n the preceding deal, discards were secured by leading out high cards in the suit which was to offer the discarding opportunity. Sometimes, however, the suit on which 1 or more losing tricks are to be discarded must first be established. A high card must be driven out of the Opponents' hands. The situation can usually be properly appraised by considering the time element of leads and realizing what may happen if you thoughtlessly present the lead to an Opponent. In the following deal it will take but one lead of trumps by South to send his four spade contract down the river.|
PG| ***** 60 ***** |


NT||
pn|You,,,|st||SK|S|md|1SQJT98HJ2DKQ4CAK2,SAKHT943DT85CQJT4,S7653HKQ8DA62C983,S42HA765DJ973C765|RH||AH|Board 4|mb|1np2hp2sp3np4sppp|pc|cQ|NT|^B@2
